<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1323,1537,1883]" lastBlockId="8.[264,1323,284,1756]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Head much narrower than pronotum, crown short, of uniform length or a little longer medially than laterally, concave, anterior margin slightly upturned (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1278,1617,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[281,1294,343,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[264,1323,326,1759]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Species of Krisna. 20 – 26. Head and thorax, profile: 20. K. magna Baker, from Malaysia; 21. K. strigicollis (Spinola); 22. K. bakeri sp. nov.; 23. K. megha sp. nov. 24. K. raja sp. nov.; 25. K. varia sp. nov.; 26. K. walayari sp. nov.; 27 – 31. Female seventh sterna: 27. K. megha; 28. K. kirbyi (Kirkaldy); 29. K. strigicollis; 30. K. bakeri; 31. K. varia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174335/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 22, 24– 
<number box="[1248,1278,1617,1643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
) or rimmed (
<figureCitation box="[370,502,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[281,1294,343,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[264,1323,326,1759]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Species of Krisna. 20 – 26. Head and thorax, profile: 20. K. magna Baker, from Malaysia; 21. K. strigicollis (Spinola); 22. K. bakeri sp. nov.; 23. K. megha sp. nov. 24. K. raja sp. nov.; 25. K. varia sp. nov.; 26. K. walayari sp. nov.; 27 – 31. Female seventh sterna: 27. K. megha; 28. K. kirbyi (Kirkaldy); 29. K. strigicollis; 30. K. bakeri; 31. K. varia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174335/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Figs 20, 21</figureCitation>
) (as in 
<taxonomicName box="[588,720,1657,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colorata">
<emphasis box="[588,720,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">K. colorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[735,855,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName box="[735,851,1657,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">K. magna</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and male 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1134,1657,1682]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Siva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigicollis">
<emphasis box="[975,1134,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">K. strigicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), disc obliquely striated, coronal sulcus distinct. Face rather flat, rugose, upper margin transversely striated, lower part of face broadly parabolic in outline. Clypellus strongly broadened apicad, with faint median keel. Frontoclypeus moderately broadening upward, densely rugose. Lora small, slightly concave, wrinkled. Genae broad, wrinkled only very slightly insinuated near eyes. Ocellocular area narrow, transversely striate. Antennal ledges carinate, extending to frontoclypeus; antennal pits shallow. Ocelli in upper margin of face, near eyes placed either very close to adjacent eye or at a distance equal to 
<number box="[1173,1210,324,350]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="0.5">0.5</number>
–1.0 own diameter from eye. Pronotum large, lateral margins narrowly carinate, foliaceous, upcurved, diverging caudad, disc moderately convex, transversely striated. Scutellum as long as or longer than pronotum, with faint microsulpture in basal region, transversely striate in apical region. Forewing punctate; appendix broad, first apical cell long and very narrow, three closed subapical cells, venation of apical part reticulate owing to several extra cross veins. Spinulation of hind femora 
<number box="[814,830,564,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[849,865,564,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[884,894,564,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
; hind tibial spinulation R 
<number box="[1200,1208,580,594]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[1218,1249,564,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="26.0">26</number>
± 
<number box="[1266,1281,564,590]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
, R 
<number box="[1314,1322,580,594]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[264,296,607,633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="12.0">12</number>
± 
<number box="[315,326,607,633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
, R 
<number box="[364,372,623,637]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[385,418,607,633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="14.0">14</number>
± 
<number box="[437,448,607,633]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
; four platellae on apical transverse row of hind basitarsus. Male with apodemes of second and third abdominal segments well developed. Male eighth sternite large, more widened in apical half, with setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,1756]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Pygophore broad, cylindrical, narrowly incised near base dorsally, pygophore lobes with numerous macrosetae, ventral margin with long process. Anal tube long, strongly tapering distally, largely membranous, apically sclerotized. Subgenital plate long, narrow, lateral margin with long hair-like setae without macrosetae. Style very long, apophysis long, narrow, slightly curved dorsally near apex with a thickening not extending half width (of apophysis) near apex (
<typeStatus box="[565,617,930,956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
<number box="[624,640,930,956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<figureCitation box="[653,743,930,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 46" captionStartId="13.[264,382,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[275,1307,349,1742]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[260,1326,326,1759]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 46. Male Krisna bakeri sp. nov. 41. Eighth sternite; 42. Ventral pygophore process. specimen from Nepal; 43. Same from Dehradun; 44. Apex of apophysis of style (type 1); 45. Aedeagus, lateral view, 46. Aedeagus, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174337/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 44</figureCitation>
, 
<number box="[754,842,930,956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="67106.0">
<figureCitation box="[754,786,930,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 65 – 71" captionStartId="20.[264,382,1577,1601]" captionTargetBox="[350,1249,324,1552]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[338,1260,312,1569]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 65 – 71. Male Krisna megha sp. nov. 65. Eighth sternite; 66. Ventral pygophore processes; 67. Apex of apophysis of style (type 1); 68. Aedeagus, lateral view; 69 – 71. Aedeagus, caudal view at arrow 1, 2, 3, respectively of fig. 68." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174341/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">67</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[797,842,930,956]" captionStart="FIGURES 101 – 108" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[339,1276,516,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[311,1282,498,1796]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 101 – 108. Male Krisna walayari sp. nov. 101 – 102. Tergal apodemes of the abdominal segments 2 and 3; 103. Subgenital plate; 104 – 105. Ventral pygophore processes, variation; 106. Apophysis of style (type 1); 107. Aedeagus, lateral view; 108. Same, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174346/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">106</figureCitation>
</number>
) or with an additional distal lobe (
<typeStatus box="[1241,1293,930,956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
<number box="[1300,1318,930,956]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
: 
<figureCitation box="[264,360,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 64" captionStartId="18.[264,382,1795,1819]" captionTargetBox="[336,1260,539,1750]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[309,1277,526,1771]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 64. Male Krisna kirbyi (Kirkaldy). 60. Genitalia, lateral view; 61. Ventral pygophore process; 62. Apex of apophysis of style (type 2); 63. Connective; 64. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174340/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[382,415,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURES 80 – 87" captionStartId="24.[264,382,1566,1590]" captionTargetBox="[341,1270,341,1565]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[312,1280,326,1568]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 80 – 87. Male Krisna strigicollis (Spinola). 80 – 81. Apodemes of the abdominal segments 2 and 3; 82. Subgenital plate; 83 – 84. Ventral pygophore process; 85. Apex of apophysis of style (type 2); 86. Aedeagus, lateral view; 87. Apex of aedeagal shaft, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174343/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">85</figureCitation>
). Connective rather T-shaped with anterior margin medially produced. Aedeagus symmetrical, with well developed preatrium, poorly developed dorsal apodeme; shaft with ventral furrowlike depressed area in which gonopore opens subapically, devoid of any appendages, sculptured or spiculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,1756]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Female seventh sternite large, about as long as sixth. First and second pair of gonapophysis as in 
<taxonomicName box="[494,585,1170,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gessius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[494,585,1170,1195]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Gessius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,1756]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis box="[312,414,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[430,510,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[430,510,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[734,825,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gessius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[734,825,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Gessius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from it as discussed under that genus. The species of 
<taxonomicName box="[547,627,1250,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,627,1250,1275]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more wide spread in the Afrotropical, Oriental and southern Palaearctic regions compared to 
<emphasis box="[754,853,1290,1315]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName box="[754,848,1290,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gessius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Gessius</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which so far occurs only in the Oriental region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,284,1756]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The species of 
<taxonomicName box="[506,586,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[506,586,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Indian subcontinent are very uniform in external features making them difficult to identify without studying the male and female genitalia. Only 
<taxonomicName box="[331,491,1450,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Siva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigicollis">
<emphasis box="[331,491,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">K. strigicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
stands out with its rimlike anterior margin of head (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1197,1450,1476]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[281,1294,343,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[264,1323,326,1759]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Species of Krisna. 20 – 26. Head and thorax, profile: 20. K. magna Baker, from Malaysia; 21. K. strigicollis (Spinola); 22. K. bakeri sp. nov.; 23. K. megha sp. nov. 24. K. raja sp. nov.; 25. K. varia sp. nov.; 26. K. walayari sp. nov.; 27 – 31. Female seventh sterna: 27. K. megha; 28. K. kirbyi (Kirkaldy); 29. K. strigicollis; 30. K. bakeri; 31. K. varia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174335/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number box="[1165,1197,1450,1476]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
), although this is not so well developed as in the Malayan 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker" authorityName="Baker" box="[891,1149,1490,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magna">
<emphasis box="[891,1065,1490,1515]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna magna</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1149,1490,1516]" name="United States Pacific Island Wildlife Refuges" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Baker</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1172,1267,1490,1516]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="11.[264,382,1757,1781]" captionTargetBox="[281,1294,343,1730]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[264,1323,326,1759]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Species of Krisna. 20 – 26. Head and thorax, profile: 20. K. magna Baker, from Malaysia; 21. K. strigicollis (Spinola); 22. K. bakeri sp. nov.; 23. K. megha sp. nov. 24. K. raja sp. nov.; 25. K. varia sp. nov.; 26. K. walayari sp. nov.; 27 – 31. Female seventh sterna: 27. K. megha; 28. K. kirbyi (Kirkaldy); 29. K. strigicollis; 30. K. bakeri; 31. K. varia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/174335/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number box="[1234,1267,1490,1516]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Siva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigicollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">K. strigicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a different 
<typeStatus box="[631,681,1530,1556]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
of style apex here named 
<typeStatus box="[995,1045,1530,1556]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
<number box="[1054,1071,1530,1556]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2.0">2</number>
, which it shares with 
<taxonomicName box="[264,369,1570,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kirbyi">
<emphasis box="[264,369,1570,1595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">K. kirbyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. All other known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[716,796,1570,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[716,796,1570,1595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the subcontinent possess a style of ‘ 
<typeStatus box="[1267,1322,1570,1596]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
<number box="[264,281,1610,1636]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1.0">1</number>
’. The abdominal apodemes will also help in the identification of species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1168,1248,1610,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1168,1248,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They are poorly developed in 
<taxonomicName box="[548,660,1650,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megha" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[548,660,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">K. megha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[667,760,1649,1675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[667,760,1649,1675]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but very well developed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1085,1244,1650,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Siva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strigicollis">
<emphasis box="[1085,1244,1650,1675]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">K. strigicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where the apodemes of the third sternite are directed anteriorly to reach the hind margin of the second sternite. A similar condition is found in some Malayan species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1204,1730,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Krisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1124,1204,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Krisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
